- Text: 8. Step-by-Step Method Statement Development
Step 1: Define the Scope of Work
0
Clearly describe the activity
Identify boundaries and exclusions
Step 2: Gather Information
0
Site conditions
Drawings and specifications
Risk assessments
Client requirements
Step 3: Break Down the Task
0
Define logical sequence of activities
0
Identify key stages of work
Step 4: Identify Hazards and Controls
•
Link to risk assessments
•
Apply hierarchy of control
Ensure controls are practical and specific
Step 5: Develop the Methodology
0
Write clear, step-by-step instructions
Include plant, equipment, and materials
•
Define safe working practices
Step 6: Define Roles and Responsibilities
0
Supervisor responsibilities
0
Operative duties
Specialist roles (e.g. banksman, permit issuer)
Step 7: Include Emergency Arrangements
•
Fire procedures
•
Spill response
•
First aid arrangements
